      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Studies show that while higher wages do increase operational costs, they often lead to lower turnover, which saves small businesses significant money on recruiting and training. The \"better staff\" argument is backed by data indicating that experienced employees provide better customer service, which can drive repeat business and offset the initial payroll increase. Ultimately, the net effect on profitability depends on your specific location's economic resilience and how quickly you can adapt your pricing strategy.",
